<Author>Pochita
<Content>Bring earplugs! Stayed at this hotel for one night before driving north to Oviedo. The hotel is very well located, within easy walking distance to the Plaza Mayor and close to a lot of shopping/dining. Good locale for older individuals- I travelled with my parents (in their 70's), and they got around easily. The street where the hotel is located can be very noisy at night (welcome to Madrid), so I recommend either bringing earplugs or asking for a room not facing the street- don't know if that's possible. Like mentioned before, the staff is friendly and unintrusive. Breakfast is fine, but you can probably also find some goodies if you venture out into the streets. We rented a car from Hertz, and their location was a short cab ride away from the hotel, which was great. I'd stay here again, especially if I want to be out and about in the center of Madrid's action, and/or want to get some shopping done at the Corte Ingles or FNAC. 
