<Author>IllinoisTravel4Fun
<Content>Location, Location, Location If you want to be in the center of it all in Madrid, the Best Western Carlos V is a great place to stay. We were able to step out of our room at 11:50 p.m. on New Year's Eve, enjoy the Puerta del Sol celebrations at midnight and be back in our room at 12:15 a.m. Subway stops for two different lines are located within a five minute walk of the hotel, and it is easy to walk to many of the major sites. Also, you can find anything you need, including groceries, at the El Corte Ingles department store just across the street. The hotel is only five stories; we had two rooms on the fifth floor, facing the back of the hotel, so our rooms were very quiet, even on New Year's Eve. (We preferred peace and quiet to a view of the street.) Rooms are small by American standards but quite comfortable by European standards. One thing to note--the beds are very firm, and that bothered a few members of our family. Bathrooms were spotless and actually had a tub as well as a shower! You don't always find that in Europe. The room decor was simple but tasteful. The lobby is small but lovely, and the breakfast room was a great place for morning coffee while glancing at the International Herald Tribune or enjoying great Spanish red wines after a hard day of sightseeing. The front desk staff was wonderful, with a special shout-out to Raphael, who staffed the front desk late afternoons and evenings. His English was excellent, and he booked us a flamenco performance at a place just a five minute walk from the hotel. All in all, we felt the Carlos V was great value (approx. 100 euro for a double room), considering the location and amenities. We'd definitely stay there again on a return trip to Madrid. 
